Description:
Great Opportunity
Great opportunity to get into the market with this terrific three bedroom home. It has recently been tastefully painted throughout and has new flooring to the bedrooms, hallways and lounge. All three bedrooms are a good size and offer built in robes. The main bedroom has a ceiling fan and overlooks the front yard. Bathroom is neat and tidy with separate shower, vanity and bath. There is a separate toilet and well appointed laundry. The kitchen is in original but well presented condition with separate dining area. The large spacious lounge has evaporative cooling and a wood fire heater for those cooler nights. There is a good size carport allowing access to the large back yard where you will find a 5m x 6m shed with power and plenty of room to move.

Description:
Unique Opportunity
Don't miss out on this unique opportunity to own this period Federation red brick home very close to Tocumwal's CBD and Murray River on a huge 2050m2 block. Once fully restored, this would bring it back to its former glory and would make an ideal Family Home, BnB, Holiday Let, Home Business - only limited by your imagination. Features include pressed tin ceilings, open fireplaces in 3 of the 4 bedrooms, and the lounge, combustion stove in kitchen, cellar also with fireplace (could be used as a wine room / tasting room / dining room), raw floorboards. The industrial sized colourbond shed is cordoned off in to two areas - a near completed 2 bedroom self-contained unit with kitchenette, provision for bathroom, combustion wood heater, split system, power & TV outlet with outdoor undercover entertaining area. The second has a 10m x 9m floor area, mezzanine deck over the unit for storage, two 4.2m high roller doors to store the vehicle(s), boat and caravan. There is also an opportunity to subdivide STCA. Be quick as this is a rare find.

Description:
Private Oasis - 5 Minutes To Town
This four bedroom double brick home is sited on approx. 2.8 acres. A private sanctuary positioned only five minutes from the heart of Barooga.
This spacious home is close to the river in a magnificent garden setting.
Good sized bedrooms all with ceiling fans; two with walk-in-robe and newly laid carpet. Fully renovated bathroom with large walk in shower, bath, good sized vanity with plenty of storage underneath.
The modern kitchen features quality appliances, breakfast bar, neutral colour pallet and cork flooring. This home has two living areas; one with a wood fire heater to keep you warm during the colder months.The kitchen looks out to the generous undercover outdoor entertaining area.Moving outdoors, the home has multiple outdoor sitting areas. The main with a pitched roof looking over the sparkling in-ground pool.
Other amenities include a huge yard; huge 11m x 9m shed with concrete flooring and power (high ceilings for truck, caravan or boat access) ; 5 meg stock and domestic delivery share from channel; 3x water tanks.
This great home is surrounded by magnificent trees with noneighbours. Enjoy privacy at its finest, Enquire today.

"COOMBE PARK" TOCUMWAL - HIGHWAY FRONTAGE
"COOMBE PARK" is situated 7km north Tocumwal on Newell Highway, comprising 127 hectares (313 acres) fully developed & recycled (access to state drainage) cropping/farming country with well placed timber/shelter belts. Subdivided into 3 main paddocks generally good boundary fencing.
Modest 3 bedroom Weatherboard & fibro home with split system air conditioners, solar hot water in attractive surrounds. Lock-up garage, machinery shed with lock-up workshop, shearing shed/barn & hay shed.
There are 391 Delivery entitlements that will remain with the property.
This property has had continuous family ownership for 111 years.
"COOMBE PARK" is offered for expressions of interest (closing 17th April 2020), with 391 MIL water entitlements offered in a separate parcel for EOI

Description:
SOUTHERN RIVERINA DAIRY - LUCERNE - FODDER - CROPPING - BREEDING - FATTENING - IRRIGATION HOLDING
*Land size: 445.34 hectares/1100.43 acres (approx.), freehold land (4x titles).
*Laser levelled flood irrigation, quality structures and irrigation development, 100ML storage dam equipped with a 3-phase electric lift pump.
*2x30ML & 1x15ML MIL delivery outlets, 1x4" stock & domestic pipeline (metered).
*5 MIL Water Entitlements & 1742 MIL Delivery Entitlements.
*Irrigation spear-point bore with 400ML Entitlement, 2x stock & domestic spear-points.
*Main residence: 40sq (approx.) four bedroom plus office, two-bathroom brick veneer home in addition to 2x 3 bedroom well maintained homes.
*Access to all homes is via the Newell Highway with Finley situated 10km North, Tocumwal 10km South & Melbourne situated 280km to the South.
*Modern 50-unit rotary dairy with electronic draft & dual head feed system, 10,600ltr milk vat, extensive concreted cow yard, large solar system.
*42-meter 100 head calf barn with DeLavel automatic robot feeder, 100,000Ltr rain water tank.
*400 cow concrete feed pad in addition to a 400-cow dry lot area.
*Earth wall silage bunkers with capacity of 2500 dry tonnes.
*Concrete commodity bunker with a capacity of 42 wet tonnes, shedding capacity of 350 tonnes (approx.) of hay, ample silo grain storage.
*Pressurised trough stock water system throughout.
*Soils consisting predominantly of red loam soils, excellent fertiliser & pasture history, 45 hectares of Lucerne.
*Formed internal laneways, strategically fenced for strip grazing (incl electric).
*Well developed and farmed by the Flemming Family since 1996 and now offered for genuine sale due to relocating vendors. Enquiry and inspections are highly recommended.
*Early agricultural access available to approved purchasers.

Min $122,440

Description:
Need Space & Room to Grow?
Located on the popular Racecourse Road in Tocumwal, this 4 acre property offers a relaxed rural lifestyle and and is only a short drive from the Murray River.
The spacious four bedroom home with bull nose verandas features timber lined cathedral ceilings with exposed beams and a spacious open living area - ideal for the growing family and for entertaining. The well appointed kitchen has a wall oven and island bench and sliding doors opening to the expansive outdoor entertaining area. Main bedroom with walk-in robe and ensuite. Ducted evaporative cooling and zoned heating.
Two large sheds, both with concrete floor and power - ideal for the tradesman. Excellent domestic bore, and spray irrigated lucerne paddocks. Offers all the room you need for horses, cattle etc.
Inspection will impress as this property represents great value!

Description:
Perfect location
This immaculate property is in a prime location and located within a short stroll of the Barooga sporting precinct and Barooga Sporties. Located on an allotment size of 793sqm, this three bedroom home has lounge area with wood heater. Laminated kitchen has ample storage and overlooks the dining area both of which offer seamless views of the rear yard. All three bedrooms have built in robes. The two way bathroom acts as a semi ensuite and has full size bath, separate shower and vanity. Climate throughout is controlled by reverse cycle ducted air conditioning, as well as an evaporative air conditioner. Externally there is a single garage and double gates providing access into the rear yard. The gardens are lush, green and low maintenance, with two spots to enjoy the serenity. One small porch area outside the dining room and the other could also be utilised as a parking bay for a boat or caravan. This home is a must to inspect and will impress its new owners.
